-- Polish Stocks: Publisher Agora, PBG Builder Active in Warsaw
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-04-02T15:53:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/polish-stocks-publisher-agora-pbg-builder-active-in-warsaw.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  advanced 0.6
percent to 2,300.97 at the 5:30 p.m. close in Warsaw, gaining
for the second day.  The following were among the most active stocks on the
Warsaw Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Agora SA (AGO)  , Poland’s largest publisher, fell 2.5
percent to 12.38 zloty, the lowest since March 22, after
Deutsche Bank AG cut its recommendation on the stock to sell
from hold.  PBG SA (PBG)   gained 3 percent to 40.2 zloty, the highest
level since March 20, as Rzeczpospolita reported Poland’s third-
largest construction company may sell property units to help pay
down debt.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw 
